# Energy Price Monitoring Project

This is a small learning project built to practice working with data pipelines, web applications, and Docker.

The project fetches electricity price data from Energinet, processes the data in Python, applies anomaly detection, and shows the results in a simple dashboard.

## Features

* Fetches electricity price data from Energinet API
* Processes and sorts time-series data
* Detects unusual price patterns
* Stores results in SQLite
* Displays results in a small Flask dashboard
* Can run locally or in Docker

## Tech Stack

* Python
* Flask
* Pandas
* Scikit-learn
* SQLite
* Chart.js
* Docker

## Run locally

```bash
python -m api.app
```

Then open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:5000/
```

## Run with Docker

```bash
docker build -t energy-ai-platform .
docker run -p 5000:5000 energy-ai-platform
```

## Purpose

The purpose of the project was to practice working with:

* API data ingestion
* preprocessing
* anomaly detection
* databases
* web development
* Docker

